steps.description:
Despite the seeming variety, the general rules of every slot are the same. Almost every slot has reels, symbols, and paylines. Advanced video slots also have special symbols, like wilds and scatters, that enhance your gameplay, activate special features like bonus rounds and free spins, and grant extra winnings. Here’s a short glossary:
Reel - a vertical line where symbols are located. Usually there are 3-5 reels in a slot, and each reel fits 3-5 symbols. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d9/1_1Reel.jpg/460px-1_1Reel.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/d/d9/1_1Reel.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Symbol - basically, any image that is used to create a winning combination along the payline. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/41/1_2Symbol.jpg/460px-1_2Symbol.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/4/41/1_2Symbol.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Payline - a virtual line that goes across the reels, usually from left to right. A win occurs when you get a certain number of matching symbols on an active payline as indicated in the game’s help screen. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0b/1_3Paylines.jpg/460px-1_3Paylines.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/0/0b/1_3Paylines.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Wild symbol - a so-called Joker in slots that substitutes other symbols to create a winning combination. For example, if you get three Cherry symbols and a Wild on an active payline, it counts as four Cherries. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a0/1_4Wild.jpg/460px-1_4Wild.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/a/a0/1_4Wild.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Scatter symbol - a special symbol in advanced slots. The special thing about it is that it doesn’t have to appear on an  active payline to trigger a win. It may be “scattered” across the reels. In most cases it also activates some kind of bonus round. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a4/1_5Scatte.jpg/460px-1_5Scatte.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/a/a4/1_5Scatte.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Bonus round - a mini-round within a slot game that grants extra winnings. It may be a simple “pick one of the three chests” game, where your pick determines the win amount, a complex multilevel videogame-like experience with shooting aliens, or anything in-between. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/1_6BonusRound.jpg/460px-1_6BonusRound.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/3/3b/1_6BonusRound.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Free spins - another form of a bonus, where you get a number of spins that don’t reduce your balance. It sometimes comes with additional features like extra Wild symbols, win multipliers, etc. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7f/1_7FreeSpins.jpg/460px-1_7FreeSpins.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/7/7f/1_7FreeSpins.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}
